Under her reign, Christian Dior expanded its U.S. licenses to 48 from 32 and tripled annual revenue to about $420 million. 

   The 43-year-old Ms. Nicholas was credited with helping to jazz up Dior's staid image, notably with the help of the racy "three Diors" -- a woman and two men -- print ads in the early 1980s. 
She was currently involved in getting Dior's first U.S. boutique launched on New York's Upper East Side by the end of the year. 

